	<head>
		<title>@jayrosen_nyu</title>
		<dateCreated>Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:02:36 GMT</dateCreated>
		<expansionState>1,2</expansionState>
		<urlPublic>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/scripting/instantOutlines/master/outlines/twitter/jayrosen_nyu.opml</urlPublic>
		<urlUpdateSocket>ws://sockets.scripting.com:1239/</urlUpdateSocket>
		<dateModified>Thu, 01 Jul 2021 20:36:49 GMT</dateModified>
		<urlInstant>http://instantoutliner.com/qe</urlInstant>
		</head>
	<body>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="Six months of investigation went into this: &quot;Day of Rage: An In-Depth Look at How a Mob Stormed the Capitol.&quot; An outstanding work of journalism and forensics. For the first time I have a grasp of the whole.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/video/us/politics/100000007606996/capitol-riot-trump-supporters.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; 

And not a single &quot;both sides&quot; note is struck." type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 20:36:11 GMT" tweetId="1410698772418600965" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410698772418600965" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Best sentence I read yesterday.

&quot;Rumsfeld started being wrong within hours of the attacks and never stopped.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2021/06/how-donald-rumsfeld-deserves-be-remembered/619334/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 17:08:45 GMT" tweetId="1410646568936615940" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410646568936615940" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="There should be a term for that state of human affairs when an event happens, there is public interest in it, people want information —  they want to consume news — but there is no news to be had because it is simply too early in the event, and what fills the vacuum is... crappy." type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 14:47:04 GMT" tweetId="1410610913367920661" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410610913367920661" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The research program I direct, @membershippzzle, is sunsetting in August. But first we're having a big event to sum up the state of membership models in news. It's online, for 2-3 hours a day, August 2-6. Hundreds already signed up across the globe. Program is taking shape too. https://t.co/5rmR8zP0op" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 14:15:52 GMT" tweetId="1410603063677657088" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410603063677657088" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Rumsfeld started being wrong within hours of the attacks and never stopped.&quot; https://t.co/pGv2mNmuaN

Recommended obituary." type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 05:07:04 GMT" tweetId="1410464950859010048" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410464950859010048" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If you missed it.

&quot;Trustees for the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill voted Wednesday afternoon at a closed session to give tenure to star New York Times writer Nikole Hannah-Jones several months after refusing to consider her proposed tenure.&quot; https://t.co/UuR0lgGEMh" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 04:25:34 GMT" tweetId="1410454510108041217" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410454510108041217" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="When it came down to the Board of Trustees being held accountable for their votes, different story. Congratulations to @nhannahjones, tenured professor. https://t.co/OM77Y7BxN9" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 22:11:03 GMT" tweetId="1410360260251078665" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410360260251078665" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Not only further to the right, but further from the real.

That's the direction in which the Republican Party is moving. Here's a report from Michigan. https://t.co/o7mjIkbuud Republican official who checked into fraud claims in the election, found none, and isn't believed." type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 20:58:47 GMT" tweetId="1410342071551004674" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410342071551004674" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="One way you know Fox is not a news network is that when Carlson makes a wild — but important-if-true — factual claim, the so-called &quot;news side&quot; doesn't confirm it, refute it, or even tell you they're working on it. A news network would not act like that. https://t.co/3Rn1e3tGxS" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 14:51:51 GMT" tweetId="1410249730395979776" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410249730395979776" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Why cover Tucker? 

@brianstelter: &quot;He hosts the single biggest gathering of GOP diehards anywhere on TV... the rest of us have to decide: Ignore what he spews, or scrutinize it and supply a reality check, knowing that's going to cause him to double down?&quot; https://t.co/JK39pIU0Vp" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 13:57:24 GMT" tweetId="1410236027327893507" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1410236027327893507" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="It’s a two-party system and one party is increasingly anti-democratic. The direction the GOP travels is not only further to the right, but further from the real. Put ‘em together - the drift away from democracy, away from reality - and the conflict with journalism is structural." type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:58:44 GMT" tweetId="1409994769808429063" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409994769808429063" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I would not sign on to this: &quot;Focusing on the supply problem is a waste of energy and resources.&quot; But I agree  that we often focus on the supply side of disinformation because the demand side is hellacious, depressing, confounding, and it makes you weep for this country. https://t.co/WSjDNVWLQG" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 19:22:20 GMT" tweetId="1409955412724625413" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409955412724625413" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Yes. Her name is @Yamiche https://t.co/WBJyD8VKsx" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:59:06 GMT" tweetId="1409949566540161031" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409949566540161031" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The top 20 NPR-affiliated public radio stations had on average a total weekly listenership of about 9 million in 2020, down 9% from 2019.
 
In 2020, the NewsHour on PBS attracted 1.2 million viewers on average, up 18% from the year before. https://t.co/yCZNnl8mKd" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:51:49 GMT" tweetId="1409947730642886664" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409947730642886664" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;Opposition media traditionally relies on traffic booms when a new party takes office, but right-wing outlets have seen some of the most precipitous declines in readership since a Democratic president took office.&quot; https://t.co/i6U0EwlM9A" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:13:09 GMT" tweetId="1409907802789789702" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409907802789789702" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="The New York Times now allows subscribers to “gift” articles to people who don't subscribe. The gifted articles won’t count towards the limited number of links that non-subscribers can click before hitting a paywall. Recipients have 14 days to read them. https://t.co/SpWBjaP4eH" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 02:19:22 GMT" tweetId="1409697972581933066" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409697972581933066" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="For 35 years I'm on the journalism faculty at NYU. We taught First Amendment. Times vs. Sullivan. Pentagon Papers. Inverted pyramid. (Google it.)

We taught &quot;Frank Sinatra has a cold.&quot; Google it!

We didn't teach: We have a two party system and one of the two is anti-democratic." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 23:25:50 GMT" tweetId="1409654302239383554" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409654302239383554" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Alright. Let’s see what you got, Trustees. https://t.co/jBDrzMTkqt" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 22:19:08 GMT" tweetId="1409637518807420935" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409637518807420935" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="He’s right . You should read it. https://t.co/MOdNkbcWCB" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 22:02:04 GMT" tweetId="1409633223999586306" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409633223999586306" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="This is a great start. Next step: A link to a longer &quot;here's where I'm coming from&quot; page with personal background, any important disclosures, and other view-from-somewhere information. Scroll down on this page to see what I mean. https://t.co/1qoPQlM6rx https://t.co/NbW14CF3fW" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:08:59 GMT" tweetId="1409589664910962690" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409589664910962690" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;The UNC-Chapel Hill Board of Trustees will vote on tenure for Nikole Hannah-Jones this week...&quot; https://t.co/lxjKbleRSM

This is good. Now board members have to emerge from behind the screen of procedure and take a clear stand. Good on @nhannahjones for pressing forward." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:12:14 GMT" tweetId="1409560284734406656" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409560284734406656" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="What's different about this piece is that it frames the campaign to flood the zone with shit (in order to undermine the possibility that Americans can share a common set of facts...) as a national security threat. https://t.co/ipVKkGqL8a Recommended." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 16:38:58 GMT" tweetId="1409551911964004358" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409551911964004358" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Read this man's plea. https://t.co/FjIQL1lQJ2" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 15:51:23 GMT" tweetId="1409539937133903876" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409539937133903876" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 27" type="calendarDay" name="27" >
				<outline text="This is a headline live on the @USAToday site now. https://t.co/LkW9tVp1gV Via @_cingraham https://t.co/ikQKUZHtn1" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 23:02:40 GMT" tweetId="1409286084895383554" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409286084895383554" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="They changed it. https://t.co/Qj6CuuUq6S" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 23:51:43 GMT" tweetId="1409298427968733184" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409298427968733184" inReplyToId="1409286084895383554" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Exactly. All in. Which is why measures stronger than fact-checking are needed from journalists. Examples include: Denial of platform. Relentlessly reminding the public what office-holders did on Jan. 6 or to further the Big Lie. Aggressive questioning that never folds or forgets. https://t.co/dpKYDKgzXa" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 22:44:44 GMT" tweetId="1409281570352074755" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409281570352074755" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Tim Lambert is the speaker. Multimedia News Director and Morning Edition host at WITF, the NPR station in Harrisburg, PA. @nprpolitics could follow its local affiliate's lead in accountability reporting https://t.co/2Q4uP93a97 but it has not done so. WITF is out there on its own. https://t.co/yIhj0nwQb2" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 20:40:25 GMT" tweetId="1409250287588679681" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409250287588679681" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;How Wikipedia deals with the lab leak theory may seem trivial. After all, practically every major newspaper, website [and] ex-late night TV host has wrangled with it in the past few months. But there's something uniquely powerful about Wikipedia.&quot; https://t.co/y8SWnk84uJ" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 18:59:07 GMT" tweetId="1409224793069604864" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409224793069604864" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If you have been meaning to inform yourself about the lab leak hypothesis, but were waiting for the right explainer that would lay out the facts minus the ideological warfare, here you go. https://t.co/GzNArbUq5C By @zeynep in her best &quot;what we know/what we don't know&quot; style." type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 17:16:03 GMT" tweetId="1409198854352875524" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1409198854352875524" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="I listened. It was hard to tell exactly what they have in mind, but... Their vision for @LATimes mixes an entertainment company, cultural institution, modern day agora, and powerhouse newsroom into a giant engagement engine for news, culture and community. To which you subscribe. https://t.co/FhSs1VI3gR" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 17:09:59 GMT" tweetId="1408834941895548934" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408834941895548934" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="It's there in a Reuters report from Thursday: the importance to Democrats of the two-tracks. https://t.co/wm65yoAM0l 

Move to Friday's AP report. Senators were described as “floored” and “frustrated” by Biden's insistence on the two track approach. Why did the AP do that? 1/2 https://t.co/LSfrdXP9z4" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 16:26:13 GMT" tweetId="1408823928454328324" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408823928454328324" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" >
					<outline text="Here's the AP: &quot;Biden’s bipartisan infrastructure deal was thrown in doubt Friday as Republican senators felt 'blindsided' by his insistence that it must move in tandem with his bigger package.&quot; https://t.co/1PhLSHt4ao

Again: Why did @AP buy the &quot;we were blindsided&quot; gambit? 2/2" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 16:26:14 GMT" tweetId="1408823930706616325" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408823930706616325" inReplyToId="1408823928454328324" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Quote from @Edsall (@ Washington Post for 25 years):

&quot;During times of big change reporters have a harder time [than academics do] finding ways both to describe it and to deal with it. Reporters are usually fixed in a language that they've been using...&quot; https://t.co/gxPZrjFieI" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 22:07:52 GMT" tweetId="1408547518229647369" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408547518229647369" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Among the people who &quot;don't know any better&quot; are reporters and editors at CNN. https://t.co/BcYav90Aah https://t.co/2uifS3hUMt" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 19:21:43 GMT" tweetId="1408505703958990848" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408505703958990848" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="You could see this coming. 

&quot;Republican senators Friday were frantically considering options as the future of the sweeping compromise appeared in doubt... Senators were described as 'stunned,' 'floored' and 'frustrated.'&quot; https://t.co/1PhLSHt4ao https://t.co/bmMaUQhEm3" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 18:46:13 GMT" tweetId="1408496771047772164" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408496771047772164" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If you need a summary of where the @nhannahjones appointment at UNC-Chapel Hill stands, @CJR has a good one today. https://t.co/AzDTBokWjf This is a story I am following closely." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 18:25:19 GMT" tweetId="1408491512154017798" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408491512154017798" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The valence of this observation (&quot;more a kind of media platform...&quot;) has only increased since March. https://t.co/VyqCmVa79G" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 17:26:24 GMT" tweetId="1408476684895019012" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408476684895019012" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The “sharia law&quot; comparison seems right to me. https://t.co/X2AbdQxT44 I'd add that the mania to root out Critical Race Theory (without knowing what it is) is an attempt at symbolic reversal of the multi-racial coalition found marching in the streets after George Floyd's murder. https://t.co/7CEXZGgSI6" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:34:02 GMT" tweetId="1408463504798007297" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408463504798007297" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="I will listen to this when I get the time. Patrick Soon-Shiong (wealthy owner, immigrant, self-made, biotech) and Kevin Merida (new editor, African-American, print and digital DNA) are an intriguing combination. They could come up with something different. https://t.co/FhSs1VI3gR" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:00:21 GMT" tweetId="1408455028302651394" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408455028302651394" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Good morning. Can someone explain to me why the Washington Post is reporting that five Republicans in the Senate have signed on to Biden's infrastructure proposal https://t.co/aO1lY8XWSl while USA Today is saying it's 21 Senators with 11 Republicans? https://t.co/S8nPJ5zDCA" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:29:09 GMT" tweetId="1408447178465550336" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408447178465550336" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="How do five Republican votes for an infrastucture plan become ten when getting ten will trigger passage via reconciliation of a huge economic package those same Republicans do not want? And that's before we factor in the Green Lanternism of anything the press calls  &quot;bipartisan.&quot;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 01:58:18 GMT" tweetId="1408243120278585345" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408243120278585345" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Small sign but a good one. @nytimes hired a technology reporter whose beat will not be tech, but specifically tech accountability. https://t.co/9gDW1jUT6M Congrats @RMac18" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 20:53:42 GMT" tweetId="1408166467129036804" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408166467129036804" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="When this event passes through the looking glass in the other direction and is presented as &quot;news,&quot; it will be a test of what journalism has learned about reporting on disinformation. https://t.co/zhlxUM5u3w" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 19:33:12 GMT" tweetId="1408146208951091203" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408146208951091203" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="&quot;The past is never dead. It's not even past.&quot; The fight over the @nhannahjones appointment shows how true that is. Read this:

&quot;The White press helped destroy democracy in the South. Black journalists developed an activist tradition because they had to.&quot; https://t.co/jTl7WZnC7q" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 17:59:16 GMT" tweetId="1408122569601990661" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408122569601990661" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="If we could give the entire file of Trump coverage grades, there would be some As, Bs, Cs, Ds, and Fs for different streams in it. For the Ivanka &amp;amp; Jared portion, a grade of F isn't enough. You would have to attach a note, &quot;please come see me about Billy's work.&quot;

What a fiasco. https://t.co/BcYav90Aah" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 14:39:29 GMT" tweetId="1408072290596790273" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1408072290596790273" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
	</opml>
